    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">

      <div class="bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-text-light leading-relaxed italic">Dolphin Centrifuge supplies industrial disc stack centrifuge systems for fish processing — separating fish oil, protein stick water, and fish meal in food-grade stainless steel separators. Operating at 7,000+ Gs, these self-cleaning centrifuges process fish cooking liquor and press water continuously, recovering high-quality fish oil and concentrating protein solubles. Based in Warren, Michigan, Dolphin Centrifuge has over 40 years of experience in food-grade centrifugal separation.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Fish Oil Processing Centrifuge -->
      <div id="fish-processing-centrifuge" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-5">Fish Oil Processing Centrifuge</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          A fish oil processing centrifuge is an <a href="/industrial-centrifuge/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] font-medium underline">industrial centrifuge</a> that separates fish oil and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fish_meal" class="text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] font-medium underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">fish meal</a> from the process water, also known as stick water. Industrial fish processing involves cooking and grinding leftover fish parts that are separated into fish oil, stick water, and protein or fish meal.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Fish oil and fish meal are both high-value byproducts of the commercial fishing industry. Efficient separation of these products from the process stream requires industrial centrifuges capable of handling the high throughput and variable feed conditions typical of fish processing operations. Dolphin Centrifuge provides complete centrifuge systems for fish oil production, fish meal recovery, surimi processing, and hydrolyzed fish protein production.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Fish Oil Processing Centrifuge Video -->
      <div id="fish-oil-video" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-5">Fish Oil Processing Centrifuge Video</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The video section demonstrates the operation of industrial centrifuge systems used in fish oil and fish meal processing applications. These centrifuge systems are designed for continuous, high-volume separation of fish oil, stick water, and protein solids from processed fish residue.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Operation -->
      <div id="operation" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-5">Fish Meal and Fish Oil Centrifuge Operation</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Fish oil centrifuges operate by using a high centrifugal force to affect the separation of the three phases of processed fish residue. These centrifuges separate Fish Oil, Fish Meal, and stick water from inedible fish processing residue. The fish residue consists of non-saleable fish parts such as skin, guts, heads, bones, offal, and fins.
        </p>
        <div class="mb-4">
          <img
            src="/images/fish-processing-centrifuge/Fish-Oil-Water-Separation-Alfa-Laval-Disc-Stack-Centrifuge-800.webp"
            alt="Fish Oil Water Separation using Alfa Laval Disc Stack Centrifuge in fish processing plant"
            width="800"
            height="533"
            loading="lazy"
            class="rounded-lg w-full"
          />
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic mt-2 text-center">Fish Oil Water Separation — Alfa Laval Disc Stack Centrifuge</p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The centrifuge generates thousands of times the force of gravity, accelerating the natural settling process. Heavier solids (fish meal) are forced to the outside of the bowl, while the lighter oil phase collects near the center. The water phase settles between the oil and solids layers. This three-phase separation happens continuously, allowing for high-throughput processing of fish residue in commercial fish processing plants.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Methods of Centrifuging in Fish Processing -->
      <div id="methods" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-5">Methods of Centrifuging in Fish Processing</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          There are two primary methods of centrifuging used in commercial fish processing operations. Each method has distinct advantages depending on the throughput requirements, the quality of separation needed, and the specific end products being recovered. Understanding these methods helps fish processors select the optimal centrifuge configuration for their specific application.
        </p>

        <div id="pre-centrifuge" class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4">Pre-Centrifuge Fish Processing Steps</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The incoming fish leftovers and water are heated in a cooker. This process sometimes uses steam to break down the raw fish and release the oil.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The cooked fish biomass passes through a screening process to separate the bulk of solids from liquids. The solids separated at this phase are proteins. This solid phase is dried and is known as a fish meal. Fish meal is a valuable product for many commercial uses in aquaculture and agriculture.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            The liquid phase from the abovementioned process consists of oil, water, and fine solids. There are two ways to separate this fluid's three phases (oil, water, and solids).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div id="tricanter" class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4">Using a Tricanter for Fish Oil Production</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The first method uses a tricanter or a three-phase decanter centrifuge to separate the oil, water, and solids simultaneously. A tricanter is a three-phase horizontal centrifuge that separates bulk solids from water and oil. So, a tricanter processing this strained fluid separates the remaining fish meal from the stick water and fish oil.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            However, there is an inherent limitation with using a tricanter due to the lower centrifugal force generated. A lower g-force may not be sufficient to efficiently separate the oil and water phases in the feed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div id="decanter-disc-stack">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4">Using a Decanter and Disc-Stack Centrifuge for Fish Meal</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The other method is a two-step process using a 2-phase <a href="/decanter-centrifuge/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] font-medium underline">decanter centrifuge</a> as the first step to de-sludge the process fluid. The decanter separates the fish meal solids from the oil and water. The oil and water fluid passes through a three-phase disc-stack centrifuge in the following step.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            The following diagram shows a fish oil and fish meal processing plant designed by Dolphin Centrifuge.
          </p>

          <a href="/images/fish-processing-centrifuge/fish-meal-oil-centrifuge-system-500.webp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <img
              src="/images/fish-processing-centrifuge/fish-meal-oil-centrifuge-system-500.webp"
              alt="Fish Meal and Fish Oil Process Flow Diagram designed by Dolphin Centrifuge"
              width="500"
              height="375"
              loading="lazy"
              class="rounded-lg w-full mb-2"
            />
          </a>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic mb-6 text-center">Fish Meal Process Flow Diagram — Dolphin Centrifuge System Design</p>

          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The disc-stack separator exerts a higher centrifugal force than the decanter, separating the fine solids and the oil from the stick water continuously. The separator discharges the fish oil and stick water through independent outlets while intermittently ejecting the fine fish meal solids.
          </p>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-[#E8A317] bg-amber-50 rounded-r-lg p-4 mb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-700 italic text-sm">
              If you have simple, routine questions: We have condensed our 40+ years of disc-stack centrifuge experience into <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge-faq/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] font-medium underline">101 Frequently Asked Questions about Disc Stack Centrifuges!</a>
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Further evaporation concentrates the separated stick water into a thick syrup. Mixing this stick-water slurry with the strained fish meal produces the final fish meal product.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Mid-Page CTA -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-[#1B3A5C] to-[#2a4f7a] rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 text-white mb-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between gap-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Need Help With Your Fish Processing System?</h3>
            <p class="text-blue-100">Our engineers will evaluate your fish oil or fish meal application and recommend the optimal centrifuge system.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/" class="bg-[#E8A317] hover:bg-yellow-500 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition whitespace-nowrap">Get a Quote</a>
            <a href="tel:+12485222573" class="border border-white text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-[#1B3A5C] font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition whitespace-nowrap">(248) 522-2573</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Polishing Centrifuge -->
      <div id="polishing-centrifuge" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-5">Fish Oil Polishing Centrifuge</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/3">
            <img
              src="/images/fish-processing-centrifuge/Hemp-Ethanol-Dewaxing-Centrifuge-C1D2-450.webp"
              alt="Food Grade Stainless Steel Centrifuge Polisher for fish oil purification"
              width="450"
              height="450"
              loading="lazy"
              class="rounded-lg w-full"
            />
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 italic mt-2 text-center">Food Grade, Stainless Steel Centrifuge Polisher</p>
          </div>
          <div class="md:w-2/3">
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              A fish oil polishing centrifuge separates the fine suspended fish meal particles and stick water to produce pure fish oil. The fish oil produced by the tricanter centrifuges contains residual water and fine suspended particles due to the lower centrifugal force exerted by a tricanter.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Fish oil polishing centrifuges are <a href="/food-grade-centrifuge/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] font-medium underline">food-grade</a>, disc-stack-type centrifuges. They could be 'manual-clean' or 'self-cleaning' type centrifuges depending on the level of contamination. The higher g-force generated by a disc-stack centrifuge, up to 7,000 g's, is adequate to separate particles down to 0.5µ level and all remaining free water.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Fish Meal Decanter Specifications -->
      <div id="fish-meal-specs" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-5">Fish Meal Decanter Specifications</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          The accompanying image shows a fish meal centrifuge type Alfa Laval NX418 Decanter Centrifuge. This model is ideal for processing up to 8 Tons per hour of minced fish and water mix.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start mb-6">
          <div class="md:w-1/3">
            <a href="/images/fish-processing-centrifuge/surimi-fish-centrifuge-400.webp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <img
                src="/images/fish-processing-centrifuge/surimi-fish-centrifuge-400.webp"
                alt="Alfa Laval NX418 Food-Grade Tricanter for Fish Oil production"
                width="400"
                height="400"
                loading="lazy"
                class="rounded-lg w-full"
              />
            </a>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 italic mt-2 text-center">Alfa Laval NX418 Food-Grade Tricanter for Fish Oil</p>
          </div>
          <div class="md:w-2/3">
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              The table below provides detailed specifications for three fish meal centrifuge models commonly used in fish processing operations. These include the Alfa Laval FPNX 309 decanter and the Alfa Laval UVNX 314 and NX 418 tricanters, each suited to different capacity requirements.
            </p>
            <div class="overflow-x-auto">
              <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
                <thead>
                  <tr class="bg-[#1B3A5C] text-white">
                    <th class="py-2 px-3 text-left font-semibold text-xs">Fish Meal Centrifuge Models</th>
                    <th class="py-2 px-3 text-left font-semibold text-xs">Alfa Laval FPNX 309</th>
                    <th class="py-2 px-3 text-left font-semibold text-xs">Alfa Laval UVNX 314</th>
                    <th class="py-2 px-3 text-left font-semibold text-xs">Alfa Laval NX 418</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 font-medium text-gray-700">Centrifuge Type</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 text-gray-700">Decanter</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 text-gray-700">Tricanter</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 text-gray-700">Tricanter</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 bg-gray-50">
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 font-medium text-gray-700">Capacity (GPM)</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 font-mono text-gray-700">10</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 font-mono text-gray-700">40</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 font-mono text-gray-700">80</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 font-medium text-gray-700">Gear Box</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 font-mono text-gray-700 text-xs">1.0 kNM Cyclo</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 font-mono text-gray-700 text-xs">2.5 kNM Planetary</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-3 font-mono text-gray-700 text-xs">2.5 kNM Planetary</td>
                  </tr>
